      • makeOrder

        public void makeOrder(java.lang.String item,
                      java.lang.String size)
               throws jxl.read.biff.BiffException,
                      java.io.IOException,
                      jxl.write.WriteException
        Performs the action of making an order for non-alterable items
        Parameters:
        item- - the item ordered from the MenuGUI
        size- - the size will be taken in as a string and converted to a double for the amount of stock left in the inventory (i.e. tall=1, grande=1.5, venti=2) The method will use the alterItemAmount method in Inventory to deduct stock accordingly
        Throws:
        jxl.read.biff.BiffException
        java.io.IOException
        jxl.write.WriteException

      • makeMixedOrder

        public void makeMixedOrder(java.lang.String item,
                           java.lang.String size,
                           java.lang.String milkType)
                    throws jxl.read.biff.BiffException,
                           java.io.IOException,
                           jxl.write.WriteException
        Performs the action of making an order for alterable items that have milk specifications
        Parameters:
        item - -the item ordered from the MenuGUI
        size - -the size will be taken in as a string and converted to a double for the amount of stock left
        milkType - -the type of milk (soy, nonfat, whole) will altered in the inventory The method will use the alterItemAmount method in Inventory to deduct stock accordingly
        Throws:
        jxl.read.biff.BiffException
        java.io.IOException
        jxl.write.WriteException
